metadata:

hadiths[23]{hadithnumber,text,reference_book,reference_hadith,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro,urdu,chapter_title_arabic}:
2927,"Narrated Ibn Abi Mulaikah:that Umm Salamah said: ""The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) would separate recitation reciting: 'Al-Hamdulillahi Rabbil-'Alamin' then he would stop. 'Ar-Rahmanir-Rahim' then he would stop. And he would recite it: 'Maliki Yawmid-Din",46,1,,,,,,ام المؤمنین ام سلمہ رضی الله عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم ٹھہر ٹھہر کر پڑھتے تھے، ,2927,
2928,"Narrated Anas:that the Prophet (ﷺ), Abu Bakr, and 'Umar - and I think he said - and 'Uthman would recite: ""Maaliki Yawmid-Din (1:)",46,2,,,,,,انس رضی الله عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم ، ابوبکر و عمر رضی الله عنہما  ( راوی ز,2928,
2929,"Narrated Anas bin Malik:""The Prophet (ﷺ) would recite: 'Anin-nafsu Bin-Nafsi Wal-'Ainu Bil-'Aini'"" (From 5:)",46,3,,,,,,"انس بن مالک رضی الله عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے پڑھا: «أن النفس بالنفس والعي",2929,
2930,"Narrated Mu'adh bin Jabal:""The Prophet (ﷺ) would recite: 'Hal Tastati'u Rabbak",46,4,,,,,,"معاذ بن جبل رضی الله عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے پڑھا «هل تستطيع ربك» ۱؎۔ \r\n\r",2930,
2931,"Narrated Umm Salamah:""The Prophet (ﷺ) would recite: 'Innahu 'Amila Ghaira Salih",46,5,,,,,,ام سلمہ ۱؎ رضی الله عنہا سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم پڑھتے تھے «إنه عمل غير صالح» ۲؎,2931,
2932,"Narrated Umm Salamah:""The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) recited this Ayah: 'Innahu 'Amalun Ghairu Salih'"" (11:)",46,6,,,,,,"ام سلمہ رضی الله عنہا سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے یہ آیت اس طرح پڑھی: «إنه عمل ",2932,
2933,"Narrated Ibn 'Abbas:from 'Ubayy bin Ka'b, that the Prophet (ﷺ) would recite: ""Qad Balaghta Min Ladunni 'Udhra"" (18:76) with heaviness (Muthaqqalah - meaning with Tashdid on the Nun in ""Ladunni)",46,7,,,,,,"ابی بن کعب سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے پڑھا: «قد بلغت من لدني عذرا» ۱؎ یعنی «لدني",2933,
2934,"Narrated Ibn 'Abbas:from Ubay bin Ka'b that the Prophet (ﷺ) recited: ""Fi 'Ainin Hami'ah"" (18:)",46,8,,,,,,"ابی بن کعب رضی الله عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے «في عين حمئة» پڑھا ۱؎۔ \r\n\r\nام",2934,
2935,"Narrated Abu Sa'eed:""On the Day of (the battle of) Badr, the Romans had a victory over the Persians. So the believers were pleased with that, then the following was revealed: Alif Lam Mim. The Romans have been defeated..."" up to His saying: '...the believers will rejoice. (30:1-4)"" He said: ""So the believers were happy with the victory of the Romans over the Persians",46,9,,,,,,ابو سعید خدری رضی الله عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  جنگ بدر کے موقع پر رومی  ( اہل کتاب نصاریٰ )  اہل فارس  (,2935,
2936,"Narrated Ibn 'Umar:that he recited the following to the Prophet (ﷺ): ""Who created you in the weakness (Min Da'f)"" So he said: ""Min Du'f"" (Another chain) with similar in meaning",46,10,,,,,,عبداللہ بن عمر رضی الله عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  انہوں نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے سامنے «خَلَقَكُمْ مِنْ,2936,
2937,"Narrated 'Abdullah bin Mas'ud:that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) would recite: ""Then is there anyone who would remember? (54:)",46,11,,,,,,عبداللہ بن مسعود رضی الله عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم «فهل من مدكر» ۱؎ پڑھتے تھ,2937,
2938,"Narrated 'Aishah:that the Prophet (ﷺ) would recite: ""Furuhun Wa Raihanun Wa Jannatu Na'im (56:)",46,12,,,,,,ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی الله عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم «فروح وريحان وجنة نعيم» ۱؎ ,2938,
2939,"Narrated 'Alqamah:""We arrived in Ash-Sham and we went to Abu Ad-Darda. So he said: 'Is there any among you who can recite for me according to the recitation of 'Abdullah?'"" He said: ""They pointed to me, so I said: 'Yes, [I (can recite)].' He said: 'How did you hear 'Abdullah recite this Ayah: By the night as it envelopes?'"" He said: ""I said: 'I heard him recite it: ""Wal-Laili Idha Yaghsha, Wadh-Dhakari Wal-Untha"" Abu Ad-Darda said: 'Me too, By Allah, this is how I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) reciting it. But these people want me to recite it: Wa Ma Khalaqa but I will not follow them",46,13,,,,,,"علقمہ کہتے ہیں کہ  ہم شام پہنچے تو ابوالدرواء رضی الله عنہ ہمارے پاس آئے اور کہا: کیا تم میں کوئی ش",2939,
2940,"Narrated 'Abdullah:""The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) recited to me: ""Indeed Allah is the Provider, The Possessor of power, the Firm."" (51:)",46,14,,,,,,عبداللہ بن مسعود رضی الله عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مجھے «إني أنا الرزاق ذو ا,2940,
2941,"Narrated 'Imran bin Husain:""The Prophet (ﷺ) recited: You shall see mankind as if in a drunken state, yet they will not be in a drunken state. (22:)",46,15,,,,,,"عمران بن حصین رضی الله عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے پڑھا: «وترى الناس سكارى وما ",2941,
2942,"Narrated 'Abdullah:that the Prophet (ﷺ) said: ""How horrible it is for one of them - or - one of you to say: ""I have forgotten such and such Ayah,' rather he was made to forget. So be mindful of the Qur'an, for - by the One in Whose Hand is my soul - it escapes from men's hearts faster than a camel from its fetter",46,16,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن مسعود رضی الله عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا: ”ان میں سے یا تم م",2942,
2943,"Narrated 'Umar bin Al-Khattab:""I passed by Hisham bin Hakim bin Hizam while he was reciting Surat Al-Furqan during the lifetime of the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ). I listened to his recitation and noticed that he recited it in several different ways, which the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) had not taught me. I was about to jump over him during his Salat, but waited until he said the Salam. When he had said the Salam, I strangled him with his upper-garment and said: 'Who taught you this Surah which I heard you reciting?' He said: 'The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) taught it to me.' I said to him: 'You lie! By Allah! The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) taught me this Surah which you were reciting.' I dragged him to the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) and said: 'O Messenger of Allah! I heard this one reciting Surat Al-Furqan in a manner different from how you taught me, and you taught me Surat Al-Furqan.' The Prophet (ﷺ) said: 'Release him O 'Umar! Recite O Hisham.' So he recited it for him as I had heard him reciting. Then the Prophet (ﷺ) said to me: 'This is how it was revealed.' Then the Prophet (ﷺ) said to me, 'Recite O 'Umar.' So I recited the recitation which the Prophet (ﷺ) taught me. The Prophet (ﷺ) said: 'This is how it was revealed.' Then the Prophet (ﷺ) said 'Indeed this Qur'an was revealed in seven modes, so recite of it what is easier for you",46,17,,,,,,مسور بن مخرمہ رضی الله عنہ اور عبدالرحمٰن بن عبدالقاری سے روایت ہے کہ  ان دونوں نے عمر بن خطاب رضی ا,2943,
2944,"Narrated Ubayy bin Ka'b:""The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) met Jibra'il and said: 'O Jibra'il! I have been sent to an illiterate nation among whom are the elderly woman, the old man, the boy and the girl, and the man who cannot read a book at all.' He said: 'O Muhammad! Indeed the Qur'an was revealed in seven modes",46,18,,,,,,ابی بن کعب رضی الله عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم جبرائیل علیہ السلام سے ملے۔ آپ ,2944,
2945,"Narrated Abu Hurairah:that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: ""Whoever alleviates a burden among the burdens of the world for his brother, Allah alleviates a burden among the burdens of the Day of Judgement for him. And whoever covers (the faults) of a Muslim, Allah covers him in the world and in the Hereafter. And whoever makes things easy for one in dire straits, Allah makes things easy for him in the world and the Hereafter. Allah is helping as long as the (His) Slave is helping his brother. And whoever takes a path to gain knowledge, Allah makes a path to Paradise easy for him. And no people sit in a Masjid reciting Allah's Book, studying it among themselves, except that tranquility descends upon them and they are enveloped in the mercy, and surrounded by the angels. And whoever is slow in his deeds, his lineage shall not speed him up",46,19,,,,,,"ابوہریرہ رضی الله عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا: ”جس نے اپنے بھائی کی کوئی",2945,
2946,"Narrated 'Abdullah bin 'Amr :""I said: 'O Messenger of Allah! In how much time may I recite the Qur'an?' He said: 'Complete it in one month.' I said: 'I am able to do more than that.' He said: 'Then complete it in twenty (days).' I said: 'I am able to do more than that.' He said: 'Then finish it in fifteen (days).' I said: 'I am able to do more than that.' He said: 'Finish it in ten (days).' I said: 'I am able to do more than that.' He said: 'Finish it in five (days).' I said: 'I am able to do more than that.'"" He ('Abdullah bin 'Amr) said: ""But he did not permit me",46,20,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمرو رضی الله عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے کہا: اللہ کے رسول! میں کتنے دنوں میں قرآن پڑھ ڈا",2946,
2947,"Narrated 'Abdullah bin 'Amr:that the Prophet (ﷺ) said: ""Recite the Qur'an in forty (days)",46,21,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمرو رضی الله عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ان سے فرمایا: ”چالیس د",2947,
2948,"Narrated Ibn 'Abbas:""A man said 'O Messenger of Allah! Which deed is most virtuous to Allah?' He said: 'Al-Hallul-Murtahil'' He said: 'What is Al-Hallul-Murtahil?' He said: 'The one who recites from the beginning of the Qur'an to the end of it, every time he sets out (on a trip)",46,22,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عباس رضی الله عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  ایک شخص نے عرض کیا: اللہ کے رسول! کون سا عمل اللہ کو ",2948,
2949,"Narrated 'Abdullah bin 'Amr:that the Prophet (ﷺ) said: ""He who recites the Qur'an in less than three (days), he does not understand it",46,23,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمرو رضی الله عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا: ”اس نے قرآن س",2949,
